00:32:32.556 --> 00:32:35.506
organizers for the opportunity to be able to present today at this

537
00:32:35.536 --> 00:32:39.496
session. So we were set up pretty nicely by Julia at the

538
00:32:39.536 --> 00:32:40.246
prior talk,

539
00:32:41.436 --> 00:32:43.756
but we're going to focus a little bit more on the

540
00:32:44.876 --> 00:32:47.676
higher risk disease entities and in the adjuvant setting here.

541
00:32:49.236 --> 00:32:53.016
So I have no disclosures. So what is inflammatory

542
00:32:53.096 --> 00:32:56.646
breast cancer? It accounts for about 2% to 4% of all breast cancers,

543
00:32:58.236 --> 00:33:01.236
and by more modern data suggests that this is more at the higher end of that

544
00:33:01.256 --> 00:33:05.156
spectrum and increasing. But more importantly, it accounts for a higher

545
00:33:05.256 --> 00:33:09.016
proportion of breast cancer mortality due to its high-risk disease

546
00:33:09.076 --> 00:33:09.636
biology.

547
00:33:10.656 --> 00:33:13.816
It's diagnosed clinically by the parameters that you see here.

548
00:33:15.436 --> 00:33:18.476
But also we know that it's a molecularly distinct and

549
00:33:18.536 --> 00:33:22.136
microenvironmentally distinct disease entity,

550
00:33:22.716 --> 00:33:23.456
leading to

551
00:33:24.596 --> 00:33:25.856
the high-risk disease

552
00:33:26.796 --> 00:33:27.776
outcomes that we're seeing.

553
00:33:29.916 --> 00:33:33.716
So here are some retrospective data showing the differences between

554
00:33:33.776 --> 00:33:36.876
IBC and non-IBC. It's important to note that a diagnosis of

555
00:33:36.956 --> 00:33:40.776
IBC results in automatic upstaging of your breast cancer to

556
00:33:41.216 --> 00:33:44.886
Stage 3. So even in a localized setting, you are a

557
00:33:44.956 --> 00:33:48.926
Stage 3 patient. And if you look specifically in this setting and

558
00:33:48.936 --> 00:33:52.796
you compare the IBC versus non-IBC patients at historical data, you can see

559
00:33:52.836 --> 00:33:55.216
the outcomes are quite disparate with

560
00:33:56.036 --> 00:33:59.886
breast cancer specific survival in one study being less than five years

561
00:33:59.916 --> 00:34:02.816
compared to 13 years in the non-IBC setting.

562
00:34:03.416 --> 00:34:07.316
Now, this has improved with more modern therapies over the last 10 to 15

563
00:34:07.356 --> 00:34:10.127
years, but the differences are still quite striking,

564
00:34:11.136 --> 00:34:14.256
highlighting a really high unmet need.

565
00:34:16.397 --> 00:34:20.136
Here we're showing a comparison of Stage 3 IBC to Stage 4

566
00:34:20.256 --> 00:34:23.897
non-IBC. And what you'll note here is that the natural history of this

567
00:34:23.937 --> 00:34:27.736
disease early on in the first few years mirrors each other.

568
00:34:28.276 --> 00:34:31.676
Suggesting that even in the localized setting, that this is really a systemic

569
00:34:31.756 --> 00:34:35.316
disease requiring systemic therapies for control.

570
00:34:38.536 --> 00:34:42.325
Hormone receptor-positive, HER2-negative IBC accounts for about

571
00:34:42.397 --> 00:34:43.897
30% to 40%

572
00:34:46.176 --> 00:34:49.406
of the entire group. And what I wanted to highlight here is that

573
00:34:49.476 --> 00:34:53.417
historically, the two-year disease-free survival for this particular subtype

574
00:34:53.836 --> 00:34:56.877
has been around 60%, and this was around 2014.

575
00:34:56.917 --> 00:35:00.746
So that's improved by a couple of ticks with more modern therapies, but

576
00:35:01.396 --> 00:35:03.256
it remains a challenging disease entity.

577
00:35:05.756 --> 00:35:09.016
So we have reason to believe that targeting the tumor microenvironment would be

578
00:35:09.276 --> 00:35:13.076
particularly fruitful in IBC. We know that it's

579
00:35:13.116 --> 00:35:16.916
enriched for many different immunosuppressive populations, particularly myeloid

580
00:35:16.976 --> 00:35:17.336
cells,

581
00:35:18.316 --> 00:35:22.156
vascular aberrations, as well as fibroblasts that act on both

582
00:35:22.196 --> 00:35:24.356
innate and adaptive immunity to restrain

583
00:35:24.376 --> 00:35:28.856
the

584
00:35:28.896 --> 00:35:32.496
tumor control. So there's rationale to think that

585
00:35:32.536 --> 00:35:36.236
immunotherapy for this particular disease would work well.

586
00:35:37.056 --> 00:35:40.926
And there's data to support this in the high-risk hormone receptor-positive

587
00:35:40.996 --> 00:35:44.056
disease setting. This was published last year showing that

588
00:35:44.116 --> 00:35:47.876
neoadjuvently blocking PD-1 blockade can increase

589
00:35:48.936 --> 00:35:52.356
the instance of pathological complete response and reduce disease burden at the

590
00:35:52.416 --> 00:35:53.186
time of surgery.

591
00:35:55.056 --> 00:35:58.716
So our hypothesis is that pembrolizumab would improve

592
00:35:58.736 --> 00:36:02.296
disease-free survival for patients with hormone receptor-positive IBC.

593
00:36:03.096 --> 00:36:06.056
These are patients who underwent neoadjuvent systemic therapy

594
00:36:06.976 --> 00:36:07.876
and radiation,

595
00:36:08.896 --> 00:36:11.396
and who have residual disease at the time of surgery.

596
00:36:12.566 --> 00:36:16.556
So this is our trial schema. Patients were enrolled, like I said, after local

597
00:36:16.576 --> 00:36:20.436
therapy as well and were planned for treatment every

598
00:36:20.456 --> 00:36:22.496
three weeks for a duration of two years.

599
00:36:23.536 --> 00:36:27.136
We treated 31 patients on this trial, and a subgroup of them were

600
00:36:27.216 --> 00:36:29.996
available for correlative analyses that I'm going to get

601
00:36:30.056 --> 00:36:34.124
into.Importantly,

602
00:36:35.004 --> 00:36:38.744
71% of these patients were RCB3,

603
00:36:39.624 --> 00:36:40.144
really

604
00:36:41.084 --> 00:36:44.924
validating the fact that IBC in general is a very hard to treat disease.

605
00:36:46.324 --> 00:36:49.864
So if you look at our top-line results with

606
00:36:50.264 --> 00:36:54.044
adjuvant PD-1 blockade plus endocrine therapy, we found

607
00:36:54.064 --> 00:36:57.564
a two-year disease-free survival of about 71%,

608
00:36:58.364 --> 00:37:01.704
improving on our historical benchmark of about 60%,

609
00:37:02.504 --> 00:37:04.284
with a median follow-up of 48 months.

610
00:37:04.344 --> 00:37:07.004
We had a median DFS of 4.2 years

611
00:37:07.764 --> 00:37:10.364
and a two-year OS of 90%.

612
00:37:12.844 --> 00:37:13.184
Now, to

613
00:37:14.584 --> 00:37:18.244
understand the determinants of a response, we had a handful of patients in which we

614
00:37:18.264 --> 00:37:21.924
had paired tumor and nodal tissue that we can send for

615
00:37:21.964 --> 00:37:25.184
sequencing, in which we did copy number analysis as well as somatic

616
00:37:25.204 --> 00:37:28.854
mutation analysis. And what we found,

617
00:37:29.124 --> 00:37:32.904
one of our striking results, is that of these six patients, the two that

618
00:37:32.944 --> 00:37:36.514
had an ongoing durable disease-free survival

619
00:37:37.424 --> 00:37:41.044
actually had a lower maximum variant allele frequency detected in their nodal

620
00:37:41.084 --> 00:37:44.784
