626
00:38:03.794 --> 00:38:07.044
I've highlighted some clones there that expanded from the primary site to the lymph

627
00:38:07.084 --> 00:38:08.954
node and some genes of interest that were altered.

628
00:38:09.524 --> 00:38:13.504
What we did find was that

629
00:38:13.544 --> 00:38:17.464
in chromosome 14, especially of the two patients who responded

630
00:38:17.664 --> 00:38:20.884
durably, that we found deletions in the area of the

631
00:38:21.084 --> 00:38:22.744
immunoglobulin heavy locus,

632
00:38:23.664 --> 00:38:27.604
really suggesting that there may be some B cell biology that's contributing to

633
00:38:27.624 --> 00:38:29.244
the response to checkpoint blockade.

634
00:38:29.744 --> 00:38:33.154
And this is interesting because there's, for the past few years now, a lot of

635
00:38:33.184 --> 00:38:37.104
pre-clinical and primary patient data suggesting that these B

636
00:38:37.144 --> 00:38:39.494
T cell interactions in the lymph node are quite important

637
00:38:40.544 --> 00:38:43.224
for responses across several solid tumor types.

638
00:38:46.104 --> 00:38:47.024
So we were able to,

639
00:38:47.864 --> 00:38:51.704
in partnership with our partners at Myriad, perform

640
00:38:52.724 --> 00:38:56.564
longitudinal sampling of 19 patients whom we were

