00:40:09.524 --> 00:40:12.764
11, had actually an interval of about 18 months, suggesting that a

663
00:40:12.784 --> 00:40:16.724
potential role in the PD-1 therapy in

664
00:40:16.764 --> 00:40:19.084
exerting some sort of disease

665
00:40:19.144 --> 00:40:22.944
control. We had a second pattern emerge

666
00:40:23.064 --> 00:40:26.984
in which patients were positive at baseline post-surgically and then showed

667
00:40:27.544 --> 00:40:30.364
signs of response to PD-1 blockade.

668
00:40:30.764 --> 00:40:31.164
This was

669
00:40:32.524 --> 00:40:36.384
importantly at the ultrasensitive range highlighted in gray here,

670
00:40:36.504 --> 00:40:40.464
below 100 parts per million. One particular patient had an

671
00:40:40.564 --> 00:40:44.444
ongoing response. Another recurred molecularly about

672
00:40:44.504 --> 00:40:47.844
a year later and clinically at 22 months.

673
00:40:49.724 --> 00:40:53.704
Finally, we had a third pattern in which we had negative ctDNA post-surgically

674
00:40:54.904 --> 00:40:58.704
