755
00:45:32.404 --> 00:45:36.244
responses to checkpoint blockade. And that's possible that's happening there.

756
00:45:36.274 --> 00:45:37.324
It's purely conjecture,

757
00:45:38.144 --> 00:45:40.584
but the spatial profiling would really help tease that out.

758
00:45:41.824 --> 00:45:43.224
Thank you. Thank you so much.

759
00:45:47.204 --> 00:45:48.504
Okay. Thank you very much.

760
00:45:48.924 --> 00:45:49.304
Thank you.

761
00:45:54.344 --> 00:45:56.264
We'll now move on to our next speaker.

762
00:45:57.764 --> 00:46:01.224
Brings me great pleasure to introduce Enrique Sanz Garcia,

763
00:46:02.204 --> 00:46:05.944
and he will be talking to us about molecular residual disease interception

764
00:46:06.224 --> 00:46:09.944
in local regionally advanced head and neck squamous cell carcinoma, the

765
00:46:09.984 --> 00:46:11.284
MERIDIAN phase two trial.

766
00:46:12.204 --> 00:46:13.964
Dr. Sanz Garcia, the floor is yours.

767
00:46:18.124 --> 00:46:19.144
Good afternoon, everyone.

768
00:46:20.344 --> 00:46:24.044
First of all, I would like to thank on behalf of my co-authors the

769
00:46:24.064 --> 00:46:27.964
opportunity to present the results of the MERIDIAN phase two study, which

770
00:46:28.024 --> 00:46:31.604
evaluates the molecular residual disease interception in patients with locally

771
00:46:31.624 --> 00:46:33.504
advanced head and neck squamous cell carcinoma.

772
00:46:35.113 --> 00:46:36.284
These are my disclosures.

773
00:46:38.144 --> 00:46:41.734
Despite multimodal aggressive therapy, locally advanced head and neck squamous cell

774
00:46:41.734 --> 00:46:45.234
carcinoma is still a very hard disease to treat,

775
00:46:45.764 --> 00:46:49.084
with recurrence rates of around 30% within the first three years.

776
00:46:50.164 --> 00:46:53.984
As in other solid tumors, detection of ctDNA after definitive

777
00:46:54.064 --> 00:46:57.824
therapy has been associated with worse outcomes, as shown by us and

778
00:46:57.884 --> 00:47:01.824
others. For instance, in the pre-MERIDIAN study, which

779
00:47:01.884 --> 00:47:05.344
has paved the way to the study I'm going to present today, we

780
00:47:05.424 --> 00:47:09.304
observed that detection of ctDNA after eight to

781
00:47:09.324 --> 00:47:12.544
12 weeks post-definitive therapy was associated with worse outcomes.

782
00:47:14.004 --> 00:47:17.904
Rivocostimib is a bispecific antibody developed by AstraZeneca

783
00:47:18.384 --> 00:47:22.124
targeting both PD-1 and TIGIT, and at this point is under

784
00:47:22.164 --> 00:47:24.044
investigation in different solid tumors.

785
00:47:25.324 --> 00:47:28.964
We hypothesize that interception with rivocostimib in MRD positive

786
00:47:29.064 --> 00:47:32.624
patients may clear ctDNA, resulting in longer

787
00:47:32.684 --> 00:47:36.644
recurrence-free survival and hopefully include increasing cure rates

788
00:47:36.704 --> 00:47:39.604
in patients with locally advanced head and neck squamous cell carcinoma.

789
00:47:41.704 --> 00:47:43.264
This is the MERIDIAN study design.

790
00:47:43.804 --> 00:47:47.784
This is a phase two, single institution investigator-initiated

791
00:47:47.844 --> 00:47:48.184
trial.

792
00:47:49.204 --> 00:47:53.084
As you can see, all patients were enrolled into part A, where they receive a

793
00:47:53.224 --> 00:47:57.084
standard definitive therapy. In this situation, either

794
00:47:57.144 --> 00:47:59.924
surgery followed by adjuvant therapy, definitive

795
00:48:00.304 --> 00:48:02.224
chemoradiation, or radiation.

796
00:48:03.384 --> 00:48:07.313
Real-time ctDNA analysis was performed during part A and B using

797
00:48:07.364 --> 00:48:09.744
a tumor informed ctDNA assay, RADAAR.

798
00:48:10.534 --> 00:48:14.264
The most important time point was at eight to 12 weeks post the end of definitive

799
00:48:14.304 --> 00:48:18.224
therapy, where this was the one that helped us

800
00:48:18.244 --> 00:48:21.944
to decide whether the patient was MRD positive, provided there was no radiological

801
00:48:21.984 --> 00:48:23.084
or clinical progression.

802
00:48:24.004 --> 00:48:27.784
If eligible, patient will be randomized three to one to receive

803
00:48:27.844 --> 00:48:31.384
six cycles of rivocostimib given every three weeks versus

804
00:48:31.444 --> 00:48:35.354
observation, with real-time ctDNA analysis provided at part C and

805
00:48:35.384 --> 00:48:36.944
the first two time points of part D.

806
00:48:37.964 --> 00:48:41.624
The remaining patients will be enrolled into MRD negative part E,

807
00:48:42.064 --> 00:48:45.584
and they have a retrospective analysis of plasma collected two to six

808
00:48:45.624 --> 00:48:47.364
months at the end of definitive

809
00:48:47.424 --> 00:48:51.150
therapyEligible patients were

810
00:48:51.260 --> 00:48:54.530
patients with squamous cell carcinoma from the oral cavity,

811
00:48:54.700 --> 00:48:58.340
hypopharynx, larynx, and unknown primaries.

812
00:48:59.300 --> 00:49:03.160
We included patients with high risk of recurrence, stage two with radiological

813
00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:06.940
extranodal extension, stage three HPV positive, stage

814
00:49:07.000 --> 00:49:10.970
three, 4A, 4B HPV negative, as well as patients with recurrent

815
00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:13.420
head and neck squamous cell carcinoma that were

816
00:49:14.500 --> 00:49:15.860
treated with curative intent.

817
00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:20.820
Beyond ctDNA detection at the end of part B

818
00:49:20.900 --> 00:49:24.760
and no evidence of clinical and radiological progression, patients should

819
00:49:24.820 --> 00:49:28.560
have a tumor that expressed PD-L1 measured by CPS

820
00:49:29.080 --> 00:49:30.360
equal or more than one.

821
00:49:32.480 --> 00:49:36.140
As previously mentioned, we performed ctDNA analysis on real-time

822
00:49:36.620 --> 00:49:40.180
using RAD assay, which as you may be aware, is a tumor-informed

823
00:49:40.640 --> 00:49:44.300
assay which based on whole exome sequencing of the

824
00:49:44.360 --> 00:49:48.160
tumor can construct patient-specific panels that targets up to

825
00:49:48.240 --> 00:49:49.540
40 variants in plasma.

826
00:49:51.060 --> 00:49:54.100
We also performed some of the samples in a retrospective manner,

827
00:49:54.460 --> 00:49:57.920
including HPV DNA analysis using HPV sequencing

828
00:49:58.460 --> 00:50:02.080
and ultrasensitive next-generation sequencing approach for HPV DNA detection.

829
00:50:02.720 --> 00:50:06.580
And we performed that in all the samples at baseline, as well as on follow-up

830
00:50:06.660 --> 00:50:10.000
samples of patients with oropharyngeal cancer HPV driven.

831
00:50:12.120 --> 00:50:15.640
The primary endpoint of this phase two study was ctDNA clearance in

832
00:50:15.740 --> 00:50:19.220
patients with MRD positivity, defined as no detection of

833
00:50:19.260 --> 00:50:22.260
ctDNA at part D, week two and week 10.

834
00:50:23.420 --> 00:50:27.380
Other endpoints were efficacy, safety, HPV DNA

835
00:50:27.440 --> 00:50:30.980
kinetics, and quality of life and health economics that will be presented in

836
00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:31.360
another

837
00:50:32.760 --> 00:50:33.080
moment.

838
00:50:34.380 --> 00:50:38.240
Our study was designed to include 200 patients in total of three

839
00:50:38.380 --> 00:50:42.200
years, with the assumption that 30% of the patients will be

840
00:50:42.300 --> 00:50:45.780
MRD positive. That will lead to 60 patients and with a

841
00:50:45.860 --> 00:50:49.700
good estimation, with a good power and significant levels to see

842
00:50:49.760 --> 00:50:51.180
difference into both arms.

843
00:50:52.360 --> 00:50:56.140
Recruitment was paused after 52 patients because only two patients

844
00:50:56.200 --> 00:50:58.460
were able to be enrolled into part C and D.

845
00:51:01.040 --> 00:51:04.000
Here are the study disposition of the patients.

846
00:51:04.440 --> 00:51:08.200
Fifty-two patients were screened, and 42 patients were available for

847
00:51:08.340 --> 00:51:09.420
MRD at the end of part B.

848
00:51:10.300 --> 00:51:14.220
Of note, most of the patients were able to have enough tissue to perform

849
00:51:14.240 --> 00:51:18.070
whole exome sequencing. Only three patients didn't have that situation,

850
00:51:18.380 --> 00:51:21.520
and I think that's something to highlight because many of these patients didn't go

851
00:51:21.800 --> 00:51:25.700
into surgery. They were using baseline biopsies, and we were able to construct

852
00:51:25.720 --> 00:51:29.560
that panels properly. The recruitment happened between

853
00:51:29.640 --> 00:51:32.180
July 2023 and June 2025.

854
00:51:33.900 --> 00:51:36.640
These are the study characteristics of the patients enrolled.

855
00:51:36.660 --> 00:51:40.120
These are very similar to any other centers across North America,

856
00:51:40.720 --> 00:51:44.580
mainly oropharyngeal cancer, stage three, and treated with definitive

857
00:51:44.660 --> 00:51:45.450
chemoradiation.

858
00:51:46.520 --> 00:51:49.880
Detection of ctDNA at baseline was observed in

859
00:51:50.000 --> 00:51:53.820
97.4% of the patients where the tumor was in situ, while

860
00:51:53.880 --> 00:51:57.800
concordance between P16 status and HPV DNA in the plasma of

861
00:51:57.840 --> 00:52:00.660
oropharyngeal cancer patients was 96%.

862
00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:07.120
These are the disposition of the patients that were available for

863
00:52:07.200 --> 00:52:08.540
MRD at the end of part B.

864
00:52:09.400 --> 00:52:13.060
Five patients have positive ctDNA, two have equivocal results,

865
00:52:13.480 --> 00:52:17.220
and 35 patients were negative. From those patients who have equivocal

866
00:52:17.260 --> 00:52:20.830
result, one was positive four weeks after the follow-up,

867
00:52:21.360 --> 00:52:24.180
part B follow-up to sample, and another was negative.

868
00:52:25.240 --> 00:52:28.920
From the six patients who were eligible for MRD

869
00:52:28.960 --> 00:52:32.340
positivity, unfortunately, only two could go into part C,

870
00:52:32.940 --> 00:52:36.560
basically because they have radiological disease and one patient

871
00:52:36.600 --> 00:52:40.240
because it was CPS less than one.

872
00:52:40.280 --> 00:52:44.260
However, the patient who underwent treatment is currently free of disease, as I

873
00:52:44.320 --> 00:52:47.160
will show you later, and the patient who went into observation had later

874
00:52:47.240 --> 00:52:47.800
progression.

875
00:52:49.020 --> 00:52:51.920
With a median follow-up of 99.8 months,

876
00:52:52.840 --> 00:52:56.800
there is a total of 10 patients who have, at this moment, recurrence, which is

877
00:52:57.080 --> 00:52:59.480
23% of the evaluable population.

878
00:53:01.510 --> 00:53:05.500
This slide illustrates the journey through the MERIDIAN

879
00:53:05.619 --> 00:53:09.380
study of the patient who received interception therapy, which is patient

880
00:53:09.460 --> 00:53:13.300
17. This patient was diagnosed with a stage three HPV positive

881
00:53:13.380 --> 00:53:17.360
oropharyngeal cancer and was treated with the standard of care chemoradiation.

882
00:53:18.040 --> 00:53:21.660
As you can see in this graph, the ctDNA decreased

883
00:53:21.720 --> 00:53:25.550
significantly post-chemoradiation with a slight increase at the end

884
00:53:25.580 --> 00:53:28.200
of part B, making the patient eligible to undergo

